reviews_data.review_text:
Fabulous with f of fantastic, delicious with d of delightful, nice with n of need to come more often 

It's a super cozy place with a lot of variety not only of coffee, tea and smoothies but desserts MADE AT HOME, what what?! Breakfast and lunches, gluten-free options and a wide variety of flavors for coffees and tea, as well as lactose-free options 

When you arrive you feel very welcome, how to get to your grandmother's house and all those who take care of you are super kind and sweet 

There are a variety of tables and seats for you to choose to your liking and even a more private section if you need to study, work or recharge social battery ; you order at the front, they give you a little number and they bring your food to the table, the drinks are delivered to you in a window by your name  each table and their seats are different, it is a concept that I loved to die 

You can see that they are very eco-friendly in the way they serve food and drinks in biodegradable containers and/or reusable dishes and cutlery, seeing places that strive for the environment always makes me happy 

I read that they offer courses to eat better or the space for private events/meetings after working hours 

And I didn't pay much attention to it, but they have a small stand with books or notebooks and nice things like that 

Also there are super beautiful green areas all around and a lake with ducks and geese so If you prefer not to sit, you can take a walk with your drink around nature 

Everything is definitely excellent, the flavors, the attention, the decoration, the prices, around areas, this should be anybody frequent cafe
The spot is amazing! And they cook with real food, Non-GMO and Keto options!! I love it.
Nice place

I ordered DoorDash& was ordered here because of the gluten free options.I was so hoping for the turkey sandwich to be as pictured but it wasn't.It even says thick cut organic turkey breast.This was deli meat,thin sliced& processed!!
However the blueberry muffin & the brownie were excellent.I think you need to change that picture.Its very deceiving.
Love it! Can't wait to go again!
Great food, cozy ambience and overall wonderful experience.  Must visit.
The sandwiches are awesome and the atmosphere is so relaxing!  I ate there three days in a row!

Ambience is really one-of-a kind, log cabin cafe but still in the city. Just tucked away to keep up the somewhat isolated feel in a way that compliments the concept. Will be back next time to take in the lake view. Very much a hidden gem. 4 stars because the speed could be a tad faster and I got the sense the young lady taking orders was new, but we've all been there, so it's understandable.

Chatty Cathy's Cafe is absolutely awesome!  It is without doubt one of the best coffee shops ever!  The coffee was delicious.  The interior was beautiful with all the wood, lights, fireplace, and I was very amazed by the beautiful photo of our Savior Jesus Christ on the wall.  Without any doubt I strongly recommend Chatty Cathy's Cafe because it'll be more than just an enjoyable experience it'll be a great opportunity!  Have a great day, and know God loves you!
Cozy little cafe! Tasty food and coffee. It felt like we were in the mountains for a bit. We tried the breakfast burrito and maple pecan muffin.
Un lugar lindo, acogedor y comida deliciosa. Creo que podria ser un poco mas abundante por lo que conviene tenerlo en mente al pedir.
Amazing Place, Cozy vibes.
Cozy, friendly. STOP THERE EVERY TIME I CAN !
Nice shop. The coffee is 3/5 (dark roast) to me but the atmosphere and is really great. It's cozy and the staff is very nice.

This is a great place to go for a chill afternoon pick me up and bite! The interior is so adorable and homey, coffee and food were delicious!! Gluten free waffle and breakfast sandwich were super yummy. We came in from Charlotte and so glad we stopped here!

Great sandwiches, beverages, atmosphere and attentive staff. A favorite of ours and we have been all over the world. On my last few visits I have developed a favorite sandwich. It is the turkey and cranberry. Highly recommend that sandwich and the chili.
If you need a Break from life to came to this place to unwind!

Since 2020 50+ conference...looks really great,I like the ramp solution...blessings!!
Almost feel homesick...

Nice and quiet place to enjoy your breakfast or lunch.  My husband tried avocado sandwich and I got turkey sandwich, both were great. Will be coming back when its cool down to sit outside with our pups.
We hosted our Neighbors Helping Neighbors networking group this am. It's the best coffee house in our area!  So quaint but plenty of space!
If you get a good spot it's really nice coffee is good food is average, service is great
Cathy is a wonderful woman! So kind. Generous. The coffee is top shelf.
My favorite coffee shop!! It feels like an escape from the city. Cozy, mountain vibes.
Nice spot for coffee or tea.
One of my favorite places to read the Bible.
Such a cute spot to grab a coffee and spend time with friends or to grab a bite of lunch. Wonderful specialty drink options!

My wife, friends, and I had a delightful gathering at this charming establishment. I decided to try their cold brew coffee with oat milk, complemented by toasted marshmallow syrup. While the initial taste was pleasant, I found it slightly lacking in sweetness. However, the barista kindly accommodated my request for more sweetness, which made it thoroughly delightful. The ambiance exuded an eclectic and cozy country vibe. The blueberry muffin I savored was not excessively sugary, and its delectable flavor left me uncertain whether it was homemade. All in all, it was a wonderfully laid-back and enjoyable experience, filled with fun and relaxation.

We were greeted by two fine ladies behind the bar. They welcomed and understood it was our 1st time and offered and walked through their menu.

Barista was very kind and polite answers many questions and helped us to choose masala chai. Lego berry smoothie. She also helped with the line. Customers here were warm and gentle.

There's also outdoor space for dining.  Nice experience. We will visit again
Really enjoyed it.
We absolutely loved our bagel breakfast sandwiches!
I'd go here for coffee, but not for breakfast again. Avocado toast was $6.50 and got one slice of toast with not even a quarter worth avocado on it. But the coffee was good
Cute
my fav place to go with friends
Hidden gem is an understatement! Friendly staff, wonderful seating, good food, and a great atmosphere. What more could you ask for in a coffeeshop?
Cute place! Cozy and good coffee. Would go again.

I'm incredibly upset I haven't tried this place sooner. Fortunately, I ran out of coffee this morning and wanted my morning coffee. Chatty Cathy's is near my house, so I gave it a try, and I'm beyond impressed. I ordered the Keto Quiche, a breakfast burrito, blueberry muffin, four dog  treats, and two large Americanas. Everything ordered was delicious and the pups enjoyed getting a treat. I'm already wanting more of the quiche. I'm so happy I've found the perfect place.
Strawberry Banana Oat-milk smoothie was great!
The coffee was not good. The food wasn't the best
Cool place with a cozy design. A woods cottage feel to it. Good coffee and decent quiche
Me and my husband ordered the same drip coffee. His tastes fine, mine was stale and terrible, almost like day-old coffee. Did I get coffee discriminated?

Great vibe! Perfect venue for a baby shower. Our room housed 12 shower attendees comfortably. You are able to set/decorate the room up as you wish, and even use the adjoining porch, which we used for photos. We ordered the event English Tea menu with healthy options. The staff took care of the attendees very nicely. Everyone enjoyed the specialty coffee drinks(purchased separately) at the cafe and they were delivered to the room. A walk to the lake on a pretty day could be added. It was a great day for mom-to-be.
Absolutely in love with this place definitely be a frequent customer while in area next few months. Keto muffin was so good and my Latte!!!
Love Chattys for bullet proof organic coffee and gluten free / friendly treats! Great staff and food!
I really loved this hidden gem!  I got their Carmel macchiato & it was perfect.  Great place to bring your laptop & get some work done!
Very comfortable and rustic, I recommend the turkey and cranberry sandwich
Adorable place, great service!
I love the drinks and muffins and especially the specials they have everyday and I do love the Winter time special they had in 2021 the peppermint bark

Its a beautiful place, just to chill and they have the sweetest Bible, that we ordered on Amazon that day.  It's a memory, now that we are we back in Florida. My Bible will always remind me of that day, and we walked around the lake in the back. It is a relaxing place to go.
Honestly a solid place. Atmosphere is good, all amenities needed and nice staff. Main thing is the atmosphere next to a lake and very cool building.

This quaint little spot is one of Fort Mill's best kept secrets. Went in there with my mom. Lynn and Lorien made me glad that I said goodbye to Starbucks. She's used to live in New England like me so she had me at hello...;-)!
Great food

My food came out 15min before my husbands. They delivered his grilled cheese and soup to another table. Finally a waitress picked it up and took it to the back. Two minutes later they bring it to my husband! (With no spoon either)
I then went to ask the manager for a spoon and If the sandwich was the same one from the other table. She said "no we'd never do that!" Meanwhile, my husband said his sandwich was NOT hot at all!
So they lied. Too bad bc good food and cute place but can't trust them.

Beautiful spot.
Coffee and smoothie were wonderful.
The atmosphere and service was even better.
I will tell others about this relaxing purveyor of caffeinated joy.

This place is great! The coffee is delicious and Cathy is always fun to talk to. I met Paige today. She has a great personality and is going on vacation today after work, so if you stop by today, be sure to wish her safe travels.
I love the atmosphere and the food. Thank you for such a lovely experience. I will be back whenever I am in town.

My family and I were out for a walk and discovered chatty Cathy's coffeehouse. We decided to stop in and get two Americanos and one lavender lemonade. I got an Americano with coconut milk and hazelnut syrup with an extra shot my husband got an Americano with raspberry syrup and oat milk. They taste like the beans were over roasted and or there was not enough coffee flavor kind of like water down or day-old leftover coffee. So I went back inside to try to see what the resolution could be. She re-made the drinks of course using all of the same ingredients so in the end they all came out the same. So I don't recommend if you're a real coffee person I don't recommend chatty Cathy's on Causeway in Fort Mill South Carolina. There was no resolution other than just remaking the drinks. She got the $15 sale but I'm sharing my priceless experience. EPIC FAIL
Cute little cabin coffee shop
Amazing place loved it from the minute I walked up ! Great specials , super friendly staff, nice selection.
This place is a great alternative to the coffee behemoths like Starbucks.  Great chai and yummy cheesecake. Friendly staff.
Very friendly staff...
Brilliant coffee, breakfast sandwich was so tasty. Only visiting the state but if I was local I'd be here all the time!

Hidden gem!! Has tons of spots to sit inside and out, would be great for studying, writing, or a coffee date because it doesn't have music blasting. They have healthy fresh food options and use locally roasted coffee beans. I got the decaf iced coffee and my friend got a lavender latte. Friendly staff too.

I really like the atmosphere, good coffee, and nice interior. This is a good place to study or chill with friends. The coffee and food were all tasty and worthwhile. I like that this place is cozy with beautiful decor, but what I love the most is the music playlist(Indie), and the customer service. They are very courteous and always received me with a smile.
Cute little cafe with indoor and outdoor seating. They offer gluten-free, keto options, and many other healthy food/drink choices.
Wonderful coffee shop. They use great ingredients. It's a little off the beaten path, but well worth a visit.

Cute place, but please please please post allergens on your menu. I almost went into anaphylactic shock this morning because of your multigrain English muffin with all kinds of seeds in it is just called "English muffin."

Beautiful place for a cup of coffee with a rustic interior and tables outside. Unfortunately, we were very confused as to if you make your own coffee or if there was wait staff. They did not have coffee made. They made cheap grocerie store type bagles. Nope not going back. Better costomer servie please.

Great regular coffee. This structure was originally built as a log cabin (now with a brick exterior facade) that makes a cozy, comfortable place inside to meet friends. Pleasant staff too! After coffee, take a walk around the lake adjacent to the coffee shop.

Stopped by recently and ordered a cappuccino and a smoothie. There were two people behind the counter and they were very nice. The young lady that took my order wanted to be absolutely certain that all I wanted was a plain cap, which I'm used to now, so it was fine. lol

The cap was pretty good. Good espresso shot and the right amount of steamed milk. My wife thought that the smoothie was not so great. Sorta like chewing on oatmeal, but we chalked it up to the healthy side of things at the counter.

The only problem was that service was profoundly slow after the order was placed. I don't know how many pending orders were placed when we arrived, but in the nearly 15 minutes we waited I only saw one drink arrive at the window. I was by no means in a hurry, but that's a long time. They also didn't announce when the smoothie was up, I just happened to see it sitting there when my drink was ready and asked if it was ours.

If we lived closer I'd be inclined to try this coffee shop in the future, but their hours combined with our schedule means there just won't be an easy enough opportunity to try to make it back.
A very cute coffee house and not too overpriced. Also a great path around a pond right near by
Cute little coffee shop. All workers were friendly and welcoming. Will be back!
Vkusno no ochen' dolgo delaiut kofe. Kapuchino zhdala minut 7-10 khot' pered mnoi ne bylo nikogo s zakazom. I tak uzhe ne v pervyi raz.

This place is so cute!!! I selfishly don't even want to write a review because I don't want more people to go and find out about it, but that's not very nice is it. Lovely little coffee spot, will be back for sure!

really nice layout they had a handicap access little confused about which door to go into from where I was coming from.Seems short staffed,As we know when you're shortstaffed you can't fully do customer service like it should be &lose customers.So I ordered a smoothie a multi grain cheese sandwich and a blueberry muffin & a smoothie.They were OK the cheese was poorly Taste I asked them to put a tomato n the cheese sandwich they didn't do that the chips taste stale the muffin was OK it was poorly wrapped but these are things that happen when you're short staffed and you get the wrong impression.Then it seemed as if the Little lady that was greeting me didn't really know what she was doing & not genuine N customer service-but the other lady that was making the food seem to be getting things together.. so this is my first visit and these words may change stay tuned..
Nice place to grab a coffee and meet up w a friend or two.  I didn't eat, but they had a nice assortment of  baked goods
Delicious coffee options and fast service. It's a cute log cabin, kind of hidden in a neighborhood.
just lovely
Love the atmosphere, and the coffee is amazing! Better than any other coffeehouse, in my opinion. :)
The why is absolutely delicious! Also, the Caramel Lattes are yummy!

We were just passing through and needed some great coffee and we found it! The atmosphere and staff were amazing and I wish I could go here every day!
The coffee is phenomenal, we bought some to bring home and it's just as good as the shop I'm so in love!
Very good keto options, fresh ingredients and cheerful service. I would recommend it and come back next time I'm in the area.

We enjoy going to Chatty Cathy's for a change of scenery from our regular work from home routine. The cafe has a comfortable, cabin-in-the-mountains atmosphere with lots of cute seating options inside and out, and the bathrooms are clean. The drinks aren't always the best flavor, and the quality is not consistent (depending on who's working). Some of the baristas are not exactly "chatty" or friendly. Overall, we look past the not-so-perfect parts and keep going back because we love supporting local businesses and we want to see Chatty Cathy's succeed!
Cozy place. Great latte and the chicken salad avocado sandwich was very very good.
Such a lovely serene place to have coffee. The food was great also.
Cute coffee shop. Good variety and the coffee tastes yummy.
This place is awesome, very reasonable for organic delicious food. The staff was super friendly and informative. My friends and l will definitely be back.
Nice lil coffee shop in the neighborhood. Just got a cup of Joe

This place is so cute and a little hidden gem. They have healthy fresh food options and even have KETO drinks and meals. They are located in a quiet little neighborhood tucked near a small lake. It is sort of an odd location but my god i am glad i found it.
Staff and owner are really nice people. I definitely recommend this place! Why pay Starbucks when you can help a local business
Food was good but they messed up our order about 5 times before we finally got what we originally ordered

Good espresso!!
Cozy place!
Quaint coffee shop, friendly staff, very helpful. Will be back!

I was initially a fan of this place with its small yet very relaxing atmosphere, however, after a pretty bad customer service experience,  my view on the place is a bit tainted.
I walk in and get served by a younger African-American girl who is on her phone the entire time throughout my order. All I order is a small cold brew with almond milk and she forgets the almond milk (if there is any milk in my drink it is completely negligible to the look and taste of the drink). This is not the type of service you would expect to see from a cozy coffee shop trying to compete.
Delicious coffee, friendly staff, nice atmosphere to sit and work. Chill music playing. Made out of one of the camping log cabins from the Jim/Tammy Bakker Heritage grounds.
Great Coffee and staff. If you are in the mood for a pick me up, stop in!

Enjoying a relaxing stolen few moments together before a flight out from Charlotte.   Service is friendly, suggestions based on listening to desires to try something new and atmosphere to curb heavy thoughts! Would love to come back! Delish!
Great coffee and very rustic, relaxing.
I love coffee!  I's really cute place in a great location. I wish I could rated them higher but the coffee just average.

OMG!  Thank you for a calm coffee oasis during a visit from out of town.  Friendly and professional staff, wonderful ambiance, tasty coffee and delicious baked goods.  I can't imagine a better coffee shop "experience."  Starbucks is fine, but we prefer to support local businesses whenever we can.  Loved the chill music too.  Great place!
Shared a drink withy family and talked about old memories in the quiet shabby chic atmosphere.

I was just here a little bit ago this afternoon.  It is a nice coffee shop / Cafe.  It's decor adds a lot to the atmosphere making the place soothing and an ideal spot to want to go to more often. I got a Vanilla Iced Latte and it was delicious!
Great coffee and very friendly atmosphere! Nice and quiet and great for studying
Quality coffee with lots of options if you want a latte. Great muffins. Reasonably cheap prices considering the quality... great deal.

Super cute cabin coffee shop. Smelled amazing so we had to get the fresh baked carrot walnut muffins. Mmmm they were so good! We tried the pour over coffee which was tasty. We then took a walk around the lake and met some nice people with doggies. We had a good time.
What a great place to have coffee.

A great coffee shop to visit to break away from the norm of a Starbucks. I love that this place is a little hidden gem and it's located by a small lake/cabin community. Very cozy and and warm as you walk in and the staff were very friendly. I ordered a caramel latte with oak milk and my wife ordered the salted hazelnut with oak milk and both were equally delicious. Minimal bitterness, good mouth feel and not too sweet for it being flavored which was great. The food menu is where this place lacks but there's still solid choices. It's limited on sandwiches and what I ordered was good, I just would like more options to chose from but I understand it's a small shop. Overall I was very satisfied and I look forward to another latte soon!

Hidden gem of a coffeeshop! Barista was very friendly, coffee is fantastic. Having my first sip in the car I actually said "Oh wow" in reaction. Fresh baked muffins (delicious) and prices I thought were reasonable. Neat vibe on the inside. Certainly plan on coming back!
Coffee was great , and the service was excellent!
Very pleasant surprise.

Did someone say Keto?  In addition to their regular offerings,  the have items listed for all types of eating styles. Keto, Paleo, vegetarian.  My favorite is the keto peanut butter cake pop. Not overly sweet as some Keto options I've tried at other spots.   Definitely a regular stop for me now.
Pretty good coffees
Amazing Mocha! Loved the old log cabin it's in!

Stopped right at 8:02 but the sign said closed. I had been sitting in the parking lot at about 7:55 waiting for them to open (home coffee maker went kerplunk) As i was walking up to the door at 8:02 I noticed the sign said closed but could see a woman standing inside. Perhaps it was due to my nationality, but oh well, Starbucks was willing to accept my business.  Too bad, I really enjoy these types of coffee houses and was excited to try it.

Barely follows Covid recommendations everyone including the owner has mask below their nose and seating isn't restricted so it's basically a cesspool. Don't go here if you care the smallest bit about your health or those around you.

I cannot give a 5 until I try the food.  Love the Keto options!

I had a latte with almond milk and added lavender and vanilla syrup.  I didn't really taste the flavors but I thought the latte was one of best I've had around town.  It wasn't overly sweet (I tend to drink it black but like something different when I go out).  I appreciated that it was in a mug since I was staying there.  The barista was not very friendly but hey - she made a good cup of Joe!

I love the rustic feel of the building and there are seating options.  I look forward to visiting again.  I met Cathy and she was very sweet and helpful when my friend and I asked some questions.

Awesome place with delicious coffee and a great relaxing atmosphere. My fiance lives close by and had noticed this new coffee shop opened up so we had to give it a try! Being a coffee fanatic I can honestly say I was happy with our visit. The place has a great vibe with several spots to sit and chat or study and listen to music. The log cabin feel on the inside was homey and quaint. I got a shot of espresso, which was delicious and my cup of regular drip was well brewed also. The personnel were friendly and accommodating. The place was busy during our visit with people in and out but the staff was great to follow covid-19 precautions and kept everything disinfected and clean. All in all great visit and we will definitely be back!
Great quality, good service, nice atmosphere. Red pepper soup was very yummy. Like to have more of it.

I was definitely charged $5 or more than what I had ordered for drinks that were not good. Could not stay long as the music was so loud and people were coming in without masks. Wasn't the simple, relaxing experience I had hoped for.
Nice find! Loved the coffee. Will visit again!
Lovely atmosphere, good food.
Love the cozy ambience.
Great coffee and great atmosphere!!!

Good coffee
Easy access
Great spot, recommended
Very charming for a morning start

Love this place
, the staff is very friendly, the food, coffee and tea was perfect.. The atmosphere is quiet and relaxing..
Great organic coffee, good price, super service.
Great place.  Very clean and quaint atmosphere. Great food.

Very cute coffee spot! I love their coffee and service. It's very good coffee and I'm very picky when it comes to coffee. They have a small sandwich menu but I didn't try it yet. If you're looking for good local coffee, I would recommend checking them out. The place has cabin vibes and they have seating inside and out. Enjoy!
Great coffee house.
This is a new place and worth going to. There have amazing coffee and many organic offerings.  The people are so friendly! It has a rustic log cabin feel.
Coffee  is as good as Starbucks. It's a nice quaint place to hang out with a friend. They also sell salads, sandwiches, muffins, & keto friendly food.
Very nice atmosphere. The homemade muffins were good.
Beautiful place, very warm and friendly. Excellent choice of teas ;) , pastries & drinks. Helpful, friendly staff too. I highly recommend
It's a quiet place to wind down have great sandwiches and coffee
Great coffee and wonderful place to sit,, read,, or visit a friend!

Just went here today for the first time! Very cute place and quiet which I love! I had the iced white chocolate mocha and it was delicious. Also tried the sausage and mozzarella quiche. It was good but I don't think it was heated up for enough time. Some parts of it were cold but I was OK with it. My sister had an egg salad sandwich and said it was the best she's ever had!!
Stopped in on our walk and grabbed a latte and espresso and loved it!  Nice place!!

What a SPLENDID li'l jewel!  I was between sales meetings and ducked in here to grab a coffee, purely by chance.  After two keto chocolate muffins and a STELLAR Americano, I'm wired for sound and ready for the next consultation.  And the staff?!  Attentive, ready with recommendations for a newbie, and great company.  What a find!  Organic, healthy, and even keto options! I'm a big fan of this place and look forward to the next time I'm in town!  A+!
What an awesome neighborhood spot for coffee!
Check out their Facebook page for special events.

Great atmosphere, great coffee and tea drinks! She has a nice variety of food as well. All of her ingredients are organic and she also offers gluten free and paleo options.
The staff is kind and very helpful.
This place is awesome atmosphere. Good coffee. Very nice people. Met Cathy today, she was very nice. Can't wait to have more coffee from this place!
Nice little coffee shop in the neighborhood. Good coffee but the banana/pecan muffins were awesome!  Definitely will be coming back.
Our order was not drinkable
I've lived here my whole life and this place is a great cafe for kids and adults to bike/walk to!
Chatty Cathy's was very cozy and clean inside. Drink was tasty and prices are good.  So nice to have a coffee place to walk to in the neighborhood!
Excellent coffee, tea, food, and customer service. This coffee shop will be a staple. Beautiful rustic cabin with ample dining/meeting space is a plus too! Love it!

Beautiful welcome place!
I'm so grateful we can walk over and enjoy!
It was a beautiful evening!
